trans-unit.source: Represents the collection of selection choices in a <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.DataGridViewComboBoxCell"></xref>.

You can retrieve <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DataGridViewComboBoxCell.ObjectCollection> objects from the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DataGridViewComboBoxCell.Items%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property or the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DataGridViewComboBoxColumn.Items%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.DataGridViewComboBoxCell.ObjectCollection"></xref> class.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.DataGridViewComboBoxCell"></xref> that owns the collection.
Adds an item to the list of items for a <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.DataGridViewComboBoxCell"></xref>.
An object representing the item to add to the collection.
The position into which the new element was inserted.
item is `null`.
The cell's <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.DataGridViewComboBoxCell.DataSource"></xref> property value is not `null`.
The cell is in a shared row.
Adds one or more items to the list of items for a <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.DataGridViewComboBoxCell"></xref>.
One or more objects that represent items for the drop-down list.

Inserts an item into the collection at the specified index.
If <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DataGridViewComboBoxCell.Sorted%2A> is `false`, then the `index` value represents the position at which the `item` value is inserted.
If <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DataGridViewComboBoxCell.Sorted%2A> is `true`, then `index` is ignored and `item` is placed in the collection in a position determined by the sorting order.
